BLUETONGUE - EUROPE (29): CROATIA, ITALY SPREAD, SEROTYPE 1, OIE
****************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Thu 4 Dec 2014
Source: OIE, WAHID weekly disease information 2014; 27(49) [edited]
http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=16685


Bluetongue, Croatia
--------------------
Information received on [and dated] 4 Dec 2014 from Dr Mirjana Matausic-Pisl, Assistant to Minister, Ministry of Agriculture, Veterinary Directorate, Ministry of Agriculture, Zagreb, Croatia

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 5 Nov 2014
Date of pre-confirmation of the event: 7 Nov 2014
Reason for notification: New strain of a listed disease
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: Bluetongue virus
Serotype: 1
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (basic), laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to the whole country.

New outbreaks (1)
Summary of outbreaks: Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1: Ivinj, Tisno, Sibensko-Kninska
Date of start of the outbreak: 5 Nov 2014
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Sheep / 110 / 1 / 1 / 1 / 0

Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Sheep / 0.91 / 0.91 / 100 / 1.82
* Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive

Epidemiological comment: This outbreak was previously reported as part of the serotype 4 event on 14 Nov 2014 (follow-up report No. 2). Additional diagnostic methods provided by the Experimental Zooprophylactic Institute of Abruzzo and Molise "G. Caporale" in Italy confirmed the new strain as serotype 1.

Control measures
Measures applied: control of arthropods; movement control inside the country; screening; zoning; disinfection of infected premises/establishment(s); no vaccination; no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied; no other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Croatian Veterinary Institute, Split (national laboratory) / Sheep / competitive ELISA (c-ELISA) / 7 Nov 2014 / Positive
Croatian Veterinary Institute, Split (national laboratory) / Sheep / real-time PCR / 11 Nov 2014 / Positive
Experimental Zooprophylactic Institute of Abruzzo and Molise "G. Caporale" (OIE's Reference Laboratory) / seroneutralization test (SNT) / 28 Nov 2014 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

The location of this outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[This is the 1st time that BTV-1 has been reported in Croatia. According to their comments in the "Epidemiological Section" of the report, this outbreak was previously reported as part of the serotype 4 event on 14 Nov 2014 (follow-up report No. 2). Additional diagnostic methods provided by the Experimental Zooprophylactic Institute of Abruzzo and Molise "G. Caporale" in Italy confirmed the new strain as serotype 1.

Although the source of infection is not mentioned, this event could be related to the BTV-1 situation that is occurring in Italy. As was mentioned in ProMED-mail post 20141103.2924791, Italy has been experiencing a major BTV-1 epizootic since late September 2013. To date, 1123 outbreaks have been reported in Italy.

For an interactive map showing all outbreaks and links to the 26 reports submitted so far to the OIE, please go to http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review/viewsummary?reportid=14177.

Outbreak summary: Total outbreaks = 1123 (Submitted)
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Sheep / 180 638 / 10 953 / 3051 / 7 / 0
Cattle / 20 720 / 1127 / 1 / 3 / 0
Goats / 2489 / 84 / 4 / 0 / 0
Buffaloes / 308 / 16 / 0 / 0 / 0
Alpaca / 18 / 18 / 0 / 0 / 0

Based on their last follow-up report, Italy will report any new outbreak in the 6-monthly reports and will issue a final report when the disease is completely under control. The follow up report No 26 is available at http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/temp/reports/en_fup_0000016676_20141205_103239.pdf.

Vaccination is continues to be mentioned as a control measure; however, Italy has still not yet provided information on the type of vaccine used, number of animals vaccinated, etc.
The list of restriction zones per bluetongue serotype that have been demarcated by the EU Member States can be found in the following table:
- Table [updated 1 Dec 2014] http://ec.europa.eu/food/animal/diseases/controlmeasures/docs/bluetongue_restrictedzones_en.pdf.
A map showing the location of the restriction zones has been prepared:
- Map [updated 1 Dec 2014] http://ec.europa.eu/food/animal/diseases/controlmeasures/docs/bluetongue_restrictedzones-map.jpg. - Mods.CRD/AS]
